Text: What we achieved.
We approached this week to try and make progress on each "product" we owned in the project.
We were originally going to create sub-tasks for each section of project so that people can work a variety of areas in the project.
However, it has morphed into people just working on their area of the project which has worked out quite well as it's given us focus on what we need to do.
We have started on classes to process our files and getting data out of a database and visualising it onto a map.
We also had a meeting with Eric on Wednesday that clarified what type of user experience he was looking for.
The good.
As stated above, having product owners for each part of the process has been working well because it has allowed us to get started on implementing parts of the project.
Roro has been working on the things for the ETL pipline and UI for the map and it's kind of baffling how much work he gets done each day.
Bibi and Kuku have been working on some small features on the front end, PHP and the database.
I worked on creating function for transforming data and a geo-coding function that could be used to double check GPS coordinates.
Although this was a little frustrating at times, I managed to get it working which was a relief.
Communication has also continued to improved as a team with everyone responding to messages promptly.
Things to improve on as a team.
Things are going smoothly overall and I am confident we will be able to offer the client at least the MSHA data working through every aspect of our process.
However, I am a little concerned that we are adding layers of complexity each week.
Roro for example seems pretty set on trying to incorporate all the CSV into our database, which may take time and be impossible given the time frame.
However, it may be the case that I am underestimating the amount of work we can get done as a team.
To help deal with this, I will make sure to discuss our project in terms of our milestones with the team.
This will help us understand what is possible with the few weeks we have left.
Another issue is we didn't really meet up at all as a team until Friday.
I feel that having a regular schedule would allow us to have a better understanding of what everyone is working on.
To improve on this I've set up a meeting on google calendar ahead of time so that we have at least one or two team meetings to go over our ideas.
Things I could do better.
During the first half of the week I felt like I was simply executing the ideas of the stronger technical individuals in our group.
I've come to realise that this is an issue as I feel I'm not taking ownership of the project and less invested in figuring out my own solutions to issues we have.
I'm going to have to be a bit more assertive in starting parts of the projects and getting feedback, as opposed to always executing without thinking on my own.

Although I appreciate the advice of the people in my group, I have realised I also enjoy the challenge of figuring out how to do things, as opposed to simply executing something that is clearly laid out.
What would I do differently?.
This coming week I will aim to take the advice from my teammates and then do my own research to try to see if I can tweak the advice when implementing.
I hope this will help our team end up with a better product and with my own engagement with the project.
Goals for next week.

My goals for the week will be to create a dictionary class and functions to standardise names for at least the local states near Texas and generalise existing functions so that they can be used for a variety of files.
I will also be asking each our team members what they learnt to keep on top of everything that we are doing.
General thoughts and goals for next week.
The experience in this project has been very different from the first one.
I am less stressed and doing a better job of having a balance between the project and things such as exercise.
The downside of this is that my levels of engagement and enthusiasm for the project do not feel the same as before.
Although I am contributing and trying to work as well as can, I can't seem to shake the feeling that I am not doing enough for the project.
I'm sure that I am simply getting used to the whole process and is a little more routine than the first time round.
However, I'll keep doing my best and learn as much as I can and I'm sure my experience will be positive at the end of the project.
One of my teammates also told me they were feeling a bit down at the start of the week, so I will try to check up on him and make sure he is doing OK with the workload.
I wasn't exactly sure how to help him out, but I may ask for some advice if I feel it is getting serious.
Overall
